channel.title: Cleaning out your computer?
channel.description:
Hey does anyone know how to like clean out a computer?
Like permanently delete files you don't need anymore, so your computer will be faster?
I'm on a toshiba with Windows Vista.
Thanks.

item.title: Cleaning out your computer?
item.dc:creator: @jme jme
item.description:
@jme wrote:

Moparisthebest:

Be aware though that running an antivirus will make your computer substantially slower as well. So linux is the way to go.

Most antivirus programs don’t do shit anyways. Any virus I’ve ever had (2 or 3), could only be solved with mbam. I’m also careful though.

Just scan suspicious files with virusscan.jotti.org and you don’t need an antivirus.
